
Setting up the environment
==========================

To define the environment variables of SOLPS-ITER, a setup-script has to be sourced:
source setup

If you want to define any additional variables, create a script setup.local. 
The general setup-script will automatically look for this script and source it if present.

Note: 





At first compilation
====================

Check whether your <HOST> is included in SETUP/whereami.
Add new <HOST> if necessary.

Check whether default compiler for your <HOST> is set in SETUP/config.COMPILER.
Add new default <COMPILER> for your <HOST> if necessary.

Check default SOLPS-ITER compiler settings for your <HOST> and <COMPILER> in SETUP/config.<HOST>.<COMPILER>.
Create this config-file is necessary (example config-file: config.default.default).
If local modifications to these default compiler options are needed, 
create a config-file SETUP/config.<HOST>.<COMPILER>.local.


Compile instructions
====================

%% WE STRONGLY RECOMMEND ALWAYS COMPILING FROM THE TOP-LEVEL DIRECTORY OF SOLPS-ITER


Basic make-targets
------------------

In order to compile SOLPS-ITER, type either 
make
make solps

In order to compile SOLPS-ITER using MPI, type
make solps_mpi

In order to compile only a particular module, type
make <module>
where <module> is either
carre, divgeo, b25, eirene, b25eirene, uinp, triang

To create sonnet-light library, type
make sonnet-light

In order to compile a particular module using MPI, type
make <module_mpi>
where <module_mpi> can be 
b25_mpi, eirene_mpi, b25eirene_mpi 

To create the manual, type
make manual

Debug make-targets
------------------

To create debug-versions of SOLPS-ITER and its modules, following targets are defined:
make debug_solps
make debug_solps_mpi
make debug_<module>
make debug_<module_mpi>
with <module> and <module_mpi> as above.

Clean make-targets
------------------

To clean SOLPS, type either
make clean 
make clean_solps

To clean a particular module, type
make clean_<module>
make clean_<module_mpi>
with <module> and <module_mpi> as above.